941
00:47:40,260 --> 00:47:43,060
So their grammar is not like ours.

942
00:47:43,060 --> 00:47:47,140
It has very complex verbs, but simple in other ways

943
00:47:47,140 --> 00:47:49,740
compared to us.

944
00:47:49,740 --> 00:47:52,620
It's what a culture decides to represent that starts to work

945
00:47:52,620 --> 00:47:55,100
its way into the language.

946
00:47:55,100 --> 00:47:58,580
Conceptual systems, how do we interpret these things?

947
00:47:58,580 --> 00:48:00,940
Do we interpret these things strictly based on the symbols

948
00:48:00,940 --> 00:48:01,420
we see?

949
00:48:01,420 --> 00:48:05,900
Do we interpret them based on other cultural nuances?

950
00:48:05,900 --> 00:48:08,260
And these all start to form part of the language and enter

951
00:48:08,260 --> 00:48:09,780
the language in different ways.

